Investigation Overview¶

The aim of this analysis is to find out the factors that affect Borrower's application for prosperLoan. Thorough explanation on these factors will be seen in the slides below.

Dataset Overview¶

The prosperLoan data set was chosen for this exporatory analysis. It had a total of 113,937 loans with 81 variables on each loan, including loan amount, borrower rate (or interest rate), current loan status, borrower income, and many others. Most of the variables in this dataset are numeric in nature. The categorical data in this dataset are Loan Status, Closed Date, Prosper rating(numeric), Prosper rating(Alpha), among a few others. A total of 14 colums were chosen for effective visualisation in other to be able to provide adequeate insights and they are; LoanStatus,BorrowerAPR,BorrowerRate, ProsperRating (numeric), BorrowerState, EmploymentStatus,EmploymentStatusDuration,IsBorrowerHomeowner CreditScoreRangeLower, CreditScoreRangeUpper, DebtToIncomeRatio,IncomeRange,StatedMonthlyIncome,LoanOriginalAmount After thorough analysis the following insights were seen as discussed below.

(Distribution of Debt to Income Ratio)¶

The plot below shows that the distribution is a normal distribution, although it shows a lot of outliers,¶

zooming in the plot further clarified that there was a steady rise, a peak and a steady decline in the distribution of the DebtToIncomeRatio-hence, a normal distribution¶

Here we can see that there are spikes in the density of the LoanOriginalAmount Borrowed with the highest peaking above 0.00012.¶

There was a steady rise in the am ount being borrowed from 0 to 5000, thereafeter, a decline was seen. A shape rise was also noticed at 10000 and 15000 markers. The lowest amount issued out was 30000¶

(Distribution of Employment Status)¶

From this Analysis we see that, for the Employment status we had a high level of employed individuals. A highest number of individuals considered for loans were employed. A very small number of people given loan were unemployed¶

(Distribution of Borrowers' Credit Score Range)¶

The distribution of the CreditScoreRange shows a normal distribution as majority of the creditscore range is 680-699. This is to say that a credit score range of that value is a good score to be considered when loan is to be given out¶
